A coded reply.[/quote]

just thought i’d point out that you are using assert incorrectly…

its:

assert : ;

OR just

assert ;

and i DONT believe you wanted to pass ‘true’ to the constructor :\

i assume by assert Yz85Racer instanceof Faggot : true;
you meant assert Yz85Racer instanceof Faggot; perhaps because you thought the second expression was what you asserted expression 1 to be?

anyway, your assertions are highly useless due to the fact they are opaquely true due to your code’s structure.

on a side note #526 updated within 2 hours to #527 most likely due to a bug of sorts.

Which isn’t really necessary and in his case wrong.

@Freddy1990
I started with no knowledge as well It will get easier along the way, as long as you try to understand what the fields/classes mean.
Always think, why would I need this field. If you do that, you will learn the logic of the client a lot faster. Which means you can find your own fields as well etc.

I posted one here, you might want to take a look at it and extend it.
